> [Suggested description]
> An issue in Hitron HI3120 v.7.2.4.5.2b1 allows a local attacker to
> obtain sensitive information via the Logout option in the index.html
>
> ------------------------------------------
>
> [Additional Information]
> Vendor informed about the vulnerability.
>
> ------------------------------------------
>
> [VulnerabilityType Other]
> CWE-613: Insufficient Session Expiration
>
> ------------------------------------------
>
> [Vendor of Product]
> Hitron
>
> ------------------------------------------
>
> [Affected Product Code Base]
> Hitron HI3120 - 7.2.4.5.2b1
>
> ------------------------------------------
>
> [Affected Component]
> Logout option in the following address: http://192.168.0.1/webpages/index.html
>
> ------------------------------------------
>
> [Attack Type]
> Local
>
> ------------------------------------------
>
> [Impact Denial of Service]
> true
>
> ------------------------------------------
>
> [Impact Information Disclosure]
> true
>
> ------------------------------------------
>
> [Attack Vectors]
> Logout option does not work which can take a user to believe his session has ended, but keep active.
>
> ------------------------------------------
>
> [Discoverer]
> Gregory Cardoso
>
> ------------------------------------------
>
> [Reference]
> http://hitron.com
